<div class="post-33 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-hard-decisions" id="post-33">
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://handown.wordpress.com/2011/03/06/unclear-horizons/" rel="bookmark">Unclear horizons</a></h2>		<p>The time has come to leave my current corp.  I placed 45 sell orders in Syndicate using the median price as appears on <a href="http://www.eve-central.com">www.eve-central.com</a>.</p>
<p>I do not have any emotion about this; I am used to changing corps, both in real life and especially in-game, but this (no emotion) is a confirmation that I am on the right track, or should I say, I wasn&#8217;t on the right track where I was.</p>
<p>I do not know what to do.  I definitely do not have time to spend online until the end of March, due to pressing issues planetside.  After that is done, I&#8217;ll see what&#8217;s on offer.</p>
<p>Until then, have fun.</p>
<p>Yours truly</p>
<p>Handown</p>

